snippet: The strategy is renewing a debate about how effective such attacks can be in defeating the Islamic State, without measures like drying up its financial support or conducting a ground assault.
abstract: Questions arise in wake of French and Russian airstrikes against Islamic State in Raqqa, militants' de facto capital in Syria; debate centers on effectiveness of strikes without further measures including ground assault.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Hwaida Saad in Beirut.

lead_paragraph: The strategy is renewing a debate about how effective such attacks can be in defeating the Islamic State, without measures like drying up its financial support or conducting a ground assault.

headline.main: Strikes on Raqqa in Syria Lead to More Questions Than Results
headline.print_headline: Questions After Strikes on Stronghold in Syria
